`clamp` can be implemented directly from the contract:

```ts
export function clamp(value: number, minimum: number, maximum: number): number {
  if (value < minimum) {
    return minimum;
  }

  if (value > maximum) {
    return maximum;
  }

  return value;
}
```

Representative tests:

```ts
import { clamp } from "./clamp";

describe("clamp", () => {
  it("returns the minimum when value is below range", () => {
    expect(clamp(1, 3, 7)).toBe(3);
  });

  it("returns the maximum when value is above range", () => {
    expect(clamp(9, 3, 7)).toBe(7);
  });

  it("returns the value unchanged when already in range", () => {
    expect(clamp(5, 3, 7)).toBe(5);
  });
});
```

Review: no issues with this implementation relative to the stated contract. It handles all three required branches and preserves the input unchanged when it is within `[minimum, maximum]`.
